The files module
================

This module handles files
	>>> import files

		It can show    spaces and	tabs
		
and ends of lines

	>>> files.looks_like_this(test.path,[4,9])
	 4: 	>>> import files
	 5: 
	 6: 		It can show    spaces and	tabs
	 7: 		
	 8: and ends of lines
	 9: 

	>>> files.looks_like_this(test.path,[4,9],space='.',tab='|...',sol='^',eol='$',numbers=False)
	^|...>>>.import.files$
	^$
	^|...|...It.can.show....spaces.and|...tabs$
	^|...|...$
	^and.ends.of.lines$
	^$

Write some failing tests to a file
	>>> files.write_failing_test('made_earlier.test')

Which looks like this
	>>> files.looks_like_this('made_earlier.test')
	 0: Test Me
	 1: =======
	 2: 	>>> print 1
	 3: 	>>> print 2
	 4: 	3
	 5: 	>>> print 1 / 0
	 6: 	>>> print 0

Run that test through doctest to generate some failures
	>>> files.test_file('made_earlier.test')
	True

